Tory party chairman Grant Shapps has been accused of changing Wikipedia pages to promote himself and damage rivals . 
  He has denied the allegations calling them 'an extreme dirty tricks campaign' David Cameron said he has 'full confidence' in Mr Shapps and said he is doing 'a great job' Wikipedia has suspended an anonymous user who edited a number of pages linked to the party chairman . 
  He is accused of deleting embarrassing references to his past from his own page . 
  The site has also accused him of changing pages of Justine Greening and Lynton Crosby . 
  Shapps described the allegations as 'completely false and defamatory'